cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel architecture for learning classifiers, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The specific application domain is plume polyhedral learning, which involves analyzing data from plumes (e.g. smoke or gas emissions) and classifying them based on their shape. This could potentially fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL) if the plumes are represented as images or text, respectively. The use of mixture of experts is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
